The paper focuses on the implementation and performance of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for visual object classification, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of supervised learning to train the networks and the emphasis on deep hierarchical architectures suggest that the paper may also fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of back-propagation for training the networks, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions handwritten digit recognition, which is a task often studied in natural language processing (cs.CL) as well as computer vision.
